						               													<description>This game  is the re-edition of Outremer by Standard Games, but with a lot more rules and two entirely new playing modes: Strategical and Roleplaying. This is in fact a nearly totally different game, just sharing the included maps and counters (except the strategical ones).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The  game is from the series Cry Havoc with the same flavor of skirmish battle plus a grand strategical game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On the strategical game, you move your armies (not always known) on the map of Palestine and then resolve combat and siege on the Cry Havoc boards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is also a roleplaying system included where you create your character (crusader or sarracen), start with a small castle and try to fight, negociate or wed your way through those dangerous times. The roleplaying system uses Cry Havoc and Siege for battle, but adds hit points, several attributes (diplomacy, honor, charms) and the possibility to advance all members of your troops in experience, from a tiny peasant to a strong sergeant or even be appointed knight. A very interesting addition to the standard game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You require Cry Havoc, Siege, Le Ch&amp;#195;&amp;#162;teau des Templiers and La Cit&amp;#195;&amp;#169; m&amp;#195;&amp;#169;di&amp;#195;&amp;#169;vale fortifi&amp;#195;&amp;#169;e if you want to play the strategical game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Part of the Cry Havoc series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
